PACKAGE WebsocketController

The WebsocketController is responsible for handling two-way real-time data between the Frontend (FE)
and the Backend (BE).

This real-time data can be applied directly to users who access the admin BFF application, or it can be used by users
accessing from multiple other applications through the two main WebSocket channels: Upstream and Downstream.
Specifically:

    1   @MessageMapping(app-router)
        The Upstream channel used to send data from the Frontend to the BFF server.

    2.  @SendTo(topic-router)
        The Downstream broadcast channel used to send responses from the BFF server to the Frontend.

    3.  @SendToUser(user-router)
        The Downstream private channel used to send responses from the BFF server to a specific Frontend user.


In the context of the admin BFF application, the WebsocketController does not need to manage WebSocket connection
sessions, as this responsibility has already been defined in two Component classes explained in the documentation
located at: "admin/src/main/java/ti/dabble/configurations/AuthSocket/documentation"
